The Adamawa state Council of the Nigerian Union of Journalist (NUJ), has condemned the killing of Maxwell Nashion a broadcaster with Radio Nigeria Fombina FM Yola. Comrade, Ishaka Dedan, state chairman of the council described the brutal killings as unpardonable injury meted on the union. “NUJ condoles the family of the deceased, management and staff of the FRCN Fombina FMC Yola over the sad incident. The council called on security agencies beef up measures that would, stem the tide of increasing insecurity, especially kidnapping and armed robbery in the state. Mr Fidelis Jockthan, a colleague who also doubles as Secretary of NUJ, disclosed that, the deceased who was planning to marry was picked by his assailants at his resident in Lainde Badirisa in Girei LGA of the state. “The assailants did not take anything from his house, the whisked him away, tied up his hands, blind folded his eye and drop him unconscious near our station. “Some women going to farm saw him and reported to Civil Defence operatives at the station who rushed him to hospital where he later died”. DSP Suleiman Yahaya, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), vowed that the killers would apprehended and brought to justice.